All right.

00:01:49.220 --> 00:01:51.400
We're thrilled all of you could come.

00:01:51.400 --> 00:01:52.980
Well this event was initiated by

00:01:52.980 --> 00:01:55.210
the Associated Students
of Biola University,

00:01:55.210 --> 00:01:58.280
and it makes sense that
AS President Eric Weaver

00:01:58.280 --> 00:02:00.066
should give a quick welcome on behalf

00:02:00.066 --> 00:02:01.590
of the student body.

00:02:01.590 --> 00:02:05.533
Eric, come on up.
[audience applause]

00:02:10.520 --> 00:02:12.183
&gt;&gt; Good evening, everyone.

00:02:13.040 --> 00:02:17.600
Biola is a 100 year old
Christian un&amp;iversity,

00:02:17.600 --> 00:02:20.720
which desires to wrestle
with big questions

00:02:20.720 --> 00:02:23.060
in an honest and open way.

00:02:23.060 --> 00:02:27.610
In my senior year, my AS
colleague, Mark Keith, and I,

00:02:27.610 --> 00:02:30.203
thought we should sponsor
a blockbuster event

00:02:30.203 --> 00:02:33.880
that pursues the biggest question of all:

00:02:33.880 --> 00:02:37.790
it is reasonable to
believe that God exists?

00:02:37.790 --> 00:02:40.010
A proposal was presented to the Senate

00:02:40.010 --> 00:02:41.973
and the student body heartily agreed.

00:02:43.240 --> 00:02:47.660
So we invited two
acclaimed academic leaders

00:02:47.660 --> 00:02:51.073
in this area, William Lane
Craig, and Christopher Hitchens,

00:02:52.530 --> 00:02:55.000
and along with the
wonderful people from the

00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:58.100
Apologetics program, we
are thrilled to see it

00:02:58.100 --> 00:03:00.100
on display tonight.

00:03:00.100 --> 00:03:03.320
On behalf of the students
at Biola, I hope you really

00:03:03.320 --> 00:03:04.470
enjoy this event.

00:03:04.470 --> 00:03:07.837
Thank you.
[audience applause]

00:03:14.530 --> 00:03:16.398
&gt;&gt; Thank you for representing
the students, Eric.

00:03:16.398 --> 00:03:17.390
You're a senior.

00:03:17.390 --> 00:03:19.200
How's that job search
going in this economy?

00:03:19.200 --> 00:03:21.927
Is that going well?
[audience laughing]

00:03:21.927 --> 00:03:23.177
We'll give you some help.

00:03:24.450 --> 00:03:27.413
Oh no, our career services
on Biola, first rank.

00:03:29.050 --> 00:03:29.883
Thank you.

00:03:29.883 --> 00:03:31.640
Well, the students got this going,

00:03:31.640 --> 00:03:33.100
but there is one other important sponsor,

00:03:33.100 --> 00:03:34.440
and that is the program that I direct,

00:03:34.440 --> 00:03:37.390
the Master of Arts Program
in Christian Apologetics.

00:03:37.390 --> 00:03:39.400
If you like wrestling
with the big questions,

00:03:39.400 --> 00:03:41.850
the existence of God,
evidence for the resurrection,

00:03:41.850 --> 00:03:45.180
and the problem of evil,
the historical reliability

00:03:45.180 --> 00:03:47.610
of the Bible reconciling
science and faith,

00:03:47.610 --> 00:03:49.780
this really is a degree program for you.

00:03:49.780 --> 00:03:51.650
And if you're watching
at a distance and you're

00:03:51.650 --> 00:03:53.047
thinking, "I can't do
it 'cause I don't live

00:03:53.047 --> 00:03:55.550
"in Southern California,"
that's not the case.

00:03:55.550 --> 00:03:58.070
We have this amazing
distance learning program

00:03:58.070 --> 00:04:00.830
and it's really open to
anybody and you don't need

00:04:00.830 --> 00:04:02.660
to relocate to Southern California,

00:04:02.660 --> 00:04:04.660
although it was a very nice day today.

00:04:04.660 --> 00:04:05.740
You might want to consider it.

00:04:05.740 --> 00:04:09.480
Although, they've just
taxed us into oblivion,

00:04:09.480 --> 00:04:12.463
so you may wanna reconsider that.

00:04:14.216 --> 00:04:15.560
If you want to find out
about these programs,

00:04:15.560 --> 00:04:20.560
check out Biola.edu, B-I-O-L-A.edu,

00:04:21.220 --> 00:04:25.060
and go to the Christian
Apologetics page on that site.

00:04:25.060 --> 00:04:25.893
Well.

00:04:25.893 --> 00:04:27.570
How is this all gonna work tonight?

00:04:27.570 --> 00:04:28.820
It's pretty straight forward.

00:04:28.820 --> 00:04:31.910
In fact, your hand dandy
program will tell you what's

00:04:31.910 --> 00:04:34.240
going on, right up at
the top, inside panel,

00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:36.350
the program numbers one through eight.

00:04:36.350 --> 00:04:38.820
It'll guide you through
what's taking place

00:04:38.820 --> 00:04:41.593
every step of the way during the debate.

00:04:42.890 --> 00:04:44.729
So take a look at that.

00:04:44.729 --> 00:04:47.470
Toward the end, we will have
some time for questions,

00:04:47.470 --> 00:04:48.630
but as you notice there's no mics

00:04:48.630 --> 00:04:49.990
sitting up in the aisles.

00:04:49.990 --> 00:04:51.650
We are going to throw
it open to the students.

00:04:51.650 --> 00:04:53.823
We have a student section up there, bravo.

00:04:55.116 --> 00:04:57.960
[audience cheering]

00:04:57.960 --> 00:04:59.320
Students of all stripes.

00:04:59.320 --> 00:05:01.650
Now it's your job tonight to think up

00:05:01.650 --> 00:05:05.853
some tough questions, and I
expect you to actually vet them.

00:05:05.853 --> 00:05:08.450
That is, you may have learn
in school that there is

00:05:08.450 --> 00:05:10.653
no such thing as a dumb question.

00:05:11.520 --> 00:05:16.140
That is not true, okay?
[audience laughing]

00:05:16.140 --> 00:05:19.180
Not to intimidate you, but, check it out.

00:05:19.180 --> 00:05:20.013
Do a peer review.

00:05:20.013 --> 00:05:21.940
If you come with a question,
run it by the person

00:05:21.940 --> 00:05:24.070
next to you or on either side,

00:05:24.070 --> 00:05:25.670
and let's see how it goes.

00:05:25.670 --> 00:05:28.197
So we'll throw it open
for some Q and A time

00:05:28.197 --> 00:05:32.000
and our thoughtful moderator
will make sure it goes well.

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:32.833
All right.

