was actually a creation of
the Dutch Reformed Church.

01:44:00.030 --> 01:44:02.350
It was justified
theologically as the giving

01:44:02.350 --> 01:44:05.130
of a promised land to one
Christian religious tribe

01:44:05.130 --> 01:44:06.440
in which everyone else was supposed

01:44:06.440 --> 01:44:08.450
to be hewers of wood and drawers of water.

01:44:08.450 --> 01:44:10.290
It wasn't until the Dutch Reformed Church,

01:44:10.290 --> 01:44:12.690
under pressure, agreed
to drop their racist

01:44:12.690 --> 01:44:15.100
preachments of many years
that the apartheid system

01:44:15.100 --> 01:44:16.460
could be dismantled.

01:44:16.460 --> 01:44:20.600
The dictatorship in
Greece in 1967 to '74 was

01:44:20.600 --> 01:44:22.187
proclaimed by the Greek
Orthodox Church as a

01:44:22.187 --> 01:44:24.050
"Greece for Christian Greeks."

01:44:24.050 --> 01:44:25.660
The Russian Orthodox Church at present,

01:44:25.660 --> 01:44:27.070
maybe this is one of
the churches you don't

01:44:27.070 --> 01:44:29.430
recognize as Christian, I don't know,

01:44:29.430 --> 01:44:31.280
but it's currently become the body guard

01:44:31.280 --> 01:44:34.210
of the Vladimir Putin
dictatorship in Russia.

01:44:34.210 --> 01:44:36.640
They are now producing, the
Russian Orthodox Church,

01:44:36.640 --> 01:44:40.790
actual icons with halos
around them of Joseph Stalin

01:44:40.790 --> 01:44:43.360
for distribution to extreme
Russian nationalists

01:44:43.360 --> 01:44:46.760
and chauvinists for whom
the church has become

01:44:46.760 --> 01:44:49.970
the spiritual sword and butler.

01:44:49.970 --> 01:44:52.960
In Nazi Germany prayers
were said every year

01:44:52.960 --> 01:44:56.260
on the FÃ¼hrer's birthday
by order of the churches

01:44:56.260 --> 01:44:59.420
for his survival and well being.

01:44:59.420 --> 01:45:03.180
The first concordat signed
by Hitler and by Mussolini,

01:45:03.180 --> 01:45:06.550
in both cases, was with the Vatican.

01:45:06.550 --> 01:45:11.550
If you take out the word
"fascist" from any account

01:45:12.890 --> 01:45:15.990
of the 1920s and '30s, any
reputable historical account,

01:45:15.990 --> 01:45:18.050
and you insert the words
"Christian right wing,"

01:45:18.050 --> 01:45:19.550
or actually "Catholic right wing,"

01:45:19.550 --> 01:45:22.610
you don't have to change a word
of the rest of the sentence.

01:45:22.610 --> 01:45:26.070
And the third member of the
axis, the Japanese Empire,

01:45:26.070 --> 01:45:29.070
was led by someone who
actually claimed he was himself

01:45:29.070 --> 01:45:33.368
a god and to whom everyone
in Japan was a serf

01:45:33.368 --> 01:45:37.030
and had to admit his god had
indivinity and it was said

01:45:37.030 --> 01:45:39.577
to all of them, "Where would
we know without the Emperor?

01:45:39.577 --> 01:45:41.047
"How would we know what to do?

01:45:41.047 --> 01:45:42.757
"How would we know what
a right action was?

01:45:42.757 --> 01:45:46.077
"Without him there would
be screwing in the streets.

01:45:46.077 --> 01:45:48.877
"There would be chaos, no one
would know their bearings.

01:45:48.877 --> 01:45:50.800
"Without our god, we would be rudderless."

01:45:50.800 --> 01:45:52.673
Many Japanese people, in fact,

01:45:53.804 --> 01:45:57.440
it is pitiful to report,
still actually believe that.

01:45:57.440 --> 01:46:02.200
Now, I want to say, in
other words, that religion

01:46:02.200 --> 01:46:04.830
is the outcome of
unresolved contradictions

01:46:04.830 --> 01:46:07.780
in the material world, that
if you make the assumption

01:46:07.780 --> 01:46:11.330
that it's man-made then very few things

01:46:11.330 --> 01:46:13.030
are mysterious to you.

01:46:13.030 --> 01:46:15.520
If you make the assumption
that religion is man-made

01:46:15.520 --> 01:46:17.930
then you would know why.

01:46:17.930 --> 01:46:21.700
It would be obvious to you why
there are so many religions.

01:46:21.700 --> 01:46:23.970
When you make the assumption
that it's man-made you

01:46:23.970 --> 01:46:26.310
will understand why it is
that religion has been such

01:46:26.310 --> 01:46:28.350
a disappointment to our
species that despite

01:46:28.350 --> 01:46:30.840
enumerable revivals,

01:46:30.840 --> 01:46:33.140
enumerable attempts again
to preach the truth,

01:46:33.140 --> 01:46:35.200
enumerable attempts to
convert the heathen,

01:46:35.200 --> 01:46:37.540
enumerable attempt to send missionaries

01:46:37.540 --> 01:46:41.560
all around the world, that the
same problems remain with us.

01:46:41.560 --> 01:46:43.400
That nothing is resolved by this.

01:46:43.400 --> 01:46:47.270
That we, if all religions died out

01:46:47.270 --> 01:46:49.680
or all were admitted
to be false instead of,

01:46:49.680 --> 01:46:52.410
as all believers will tell you,
only some of them are false,

01:46:52.410 --> 01:46:54.480
in other words, we're
faced with the preposterous

01:46:54.480 --> 01:46:58.180
proposition that religion,
either all of them true,

01:46:58.180 --> 01:47:01.180
or none of them true, or
only one exclusive preachment

01:47:01.180 --> 01:47:02.013
is true.

01:47:02.013 --> 01:47:04.110
And none of these seem, to me, coherent,

01:47:04.110 --> 01:47:07.410
and all of these seem to be
the outcome of a man-made cult.

01:47:07.410 --> 01:47:10.030
Assume that all of them were
discredited at the same time,

01:47:10.030 --> 01:47:13.270
all of our problems would be
exactly what they are now:

01:47:13.270 --> 01:47:14.940
How do we live with one another?

01:47:14.940 --> 01:47:17.850
Where, indeed, do morals
and ethics come from?

01:47:17.850 --> 01:47:19.310
What are our duties to one another?

01:47:19.310 --> 01:47:21.660
How shall we build the just city?

01:47:21.660 --> 01:47:23.830
How shall we practice love?

01:47:23.830 --> 01:47:26.740
How shall we deal with the baser,

01:47:26.740 --> 01:47:29.277
what Darwin called the "Lowly stamp of

01:47:29.277 --> 01:47:31.950
"our original origins," which comes,

01:47:31.950 --> 01:47:35.420
not from a pact with the
devil, or an original sin,

01:47:35.420 --> 01:47:36.930
but from our evolution as well?

01:47:36.930 --> 01:47:38.640
All these questions, ladies and gentlemen,

01:47:38.640 --> 01:47:40.300
would remain exactly the same.

01:47:40.300 --> 01:47:43.450
Emancipate yourself from
the idea of a celestial

01:47:43.450 --> 01:47:45.470
dictatorship and you've
taken the first step

01:47:45.470 --> 01:47:46.370
to becoming free.

01:47:46.370 --> 01:47:47.203
Thank you.

01:47:48.104 --> 01:47:51.104
[audience applause]

01:47:55.230 --> 01:47:57.410
&gt;&gt; Dr. Craig, your closing argument.

01:47:57.410 --> 01:47:58.243
Five minutes.

01:48:07.840 --> 01:48:09.720
&gt;&gt; In my final speech I'd like to try

01:48:09.720 --> 01:48:11.872
to draw together some of
the threads of this debate

01:48:11.872 --> 01:48:15.040
and see if we can come
to some conclusions.

01:48:15.040 --> 01:48:17.770
First, have we seen any
good arguments tonight

01:48:17.770 --> 01:48:20.170
to think that God does not exist?

01:48:20.170 --> 01:48:21.640
No, I don't think we have.

01:48:21.640 --> 01:48:26.640
We've heard attacks upon
religion, Christianity impugned,

01:48:27.320 --> 01:48:29.850
God impugned, Mother Teresa impugned,

01:48:29.850 --> 01:48:33.483
but we haven't heard any
arguments that God does not exist.

01:48:34.620 --> 01:48:37.319
Mr. Hitchens seems to fail
to recognize that atheism is

01:48:37.319 --> 01:48:41.860
itself a world view and
it claims alone to be true

01:48:41.860 --> 01:48:44.650
and all the other religions
of the world false.

01:48:44.650 --> 01:48:47.400
It is no more tolerant than Christianity,

01:48:47.400 --> 01:48:49.110
with respect to these other views.

01:48:49.110 --> 01:48:54.110
He asserts that he alone has
the true world view: atheism.

01:48:54.540 --> 01:48:56.269
The only problem is he
doesn't have any arguments

01:48:56.269 --> 01:48:59.650
for this world view, he just asserts it.

01:48:59.650 --> 01:49:02.680
So it seems to me that
if you're going to have

01:49:02.680 --> 01:49:04.840
a world view and champion
it tonight you've got

01:49:04.840 --> 01:49:07.220
to come to a debate prepared
to give some arguments

01:49:07.220 --> 01:49:08.320
and we haven't heard any.

01:49:08.320 --> 01:49:11.160
He did have an argument
about evolution but when

01:49:11.160 --> 01:49:13.500
I explained that it
actually turned out to be

01:49:13.500 --> 01:49:16.030
supportive of theism,
evolution actually provides

01:49:16.030 --> 01:49:19.260
evidence for the existence of
a designer of the universe,

01:49:19.260 --> 01:49:21.200
so we've not heard any
good arguments to think

01:49:21.200 --> 01:49:22.700
that atheism is true.

01:49:22.700 --> 01:49:25.880
Now, I've presented five
reasons to think that

01:49:25.880 --> 01:49:28.640
theism is true and this is what God,

01:49:28.640 --> 01:49:31.010
or the god hypothesis does give you.

01:49:31.010 --> 01:49:32.760
He asks, "What does it give us?"

01:49:32.760 --> 01:49:36.870
It explains a broad range
of human experience,

01:49:36.870 --> 01:49:40.630
philosophical, ethical, scientific,

01:49:40.630 --> 01:49:42.980
historical, experiential.

01:49:42.980 --> 01:49:45.765
I find the attraction of
the god hypothesis is that

01:49:45.765 --> 01:49:50.765
it is so powerful in making
sense of the way the world is.

01:49:50.840 --> 01:49:54.680
For example, the god
hypothesis explains the origins

01:49:54.680 --> 01:49:56.130
of the universe.

01:49:56.130 --> 01:49:58.610
Mr. Hitchens has completed
dropped this point

01:49:58.610 --> 01:49:59.990
in tonight's debate.

01:49:59.990 --> 01:50:01.920
When we saw that in fact scientific

01:50:01.920 --> 01:50:04.600
and philosophical evidence
points to a beginning

01:50:04.600 --> 01:50:07.010
of the universe out of
nothing and therefore

01:50:07.010 --> 01:50:10.630
to a transcendent, personal
creator of the cosmos.

01:50:10.630 --> 01:50:12.580
The teleological argument.

01:50:12.580 --> 01:50:15.450
The fine tuning that is
established in the initial

01:50:15.450 --> 01:50:16.930
conditions of the universe,

01:50:16.930 --> 01:50:19.590
not to speak of in the
biological complexity

01:50:19.590 --> 01:50:20.470
that then ensued.

01:50:20.470 --> 01:50:23.000
And again, Mr. Hitchens has dropped that

01:50:23.000 --> 01:50:24.750
in the course of the debate tonight.

01:50:24.750 --> 01:50:27.310
So we have a creator and
an intelligent designer

01:50:27.310 --> 01:50:28.740
of the cosmos.

01:50:28.740 --> 01:50:29.573
Thirdly, the moral argument.

01:50:29.573 --> 01:50:34.550
We saw that without God there
are no objective moral values.

01:50:34.550 --> 01:50:37.860
And here Mr. Hitchens has
consistently distorted

01:50:37.860 --> 01:50:38.693
the argument.

01:50:38.693 --> 01:50:40.087
He's portrayed the argument as,

01:50:40.087 --> 01:50:44.027
"How would we know moral values
if we didn't believe in God?

01:50:44.027 --> 01:50:46.317
"We don't need to believe
in a tyrant in order

01:50:46.317 --> 01:50:47.757
"to define moral values.

01:50:47.757 --> 01:50:50.390
"Unbelief doesn't produce wickedness."

01:50:50.390 --> 01:50:52.290
That is all irrelevant.

01:50:52.290 --> 01:50:55.810
The point is that there is no foundation

01:50:55.810 --> 01:50:59.020
on a naturalistic world
view for the moral values

01:50:59.020 --> 01:51:01.270
and duties that we both want to affirm

01:51:01.270 --> 01:51:02.370
and he agrees with that.

01:51:02.370 --> 01:51:04.897
This is what he says and I quote, he says,

01:51:04.897 --> 01:51:07.067
"Our innate predisposition to both good

01:51:07.067 --> 01:51:10.017
"and wicked behavior is
precisely what one would

01:51:10.017 --> 01:51:12.917
"expect to find of a
recently evolved species

01:51:12.917 --> 01:51:16.037
"that is half a chromosome
away from chimpanzees.

01:51:16.037 --> 01:51:19.807
"Primate and elephant
and even pig societies

01:51:19.807 --> 01:51:22.657
"show considerable evidence
of care for others,

01:51:22.657 --> 01:51:26.677
"parent-child bonding,
solidarity in the face of danger,

01:51:26.677 --> 01:51:27.510
"and so on.

01:51:27.510 --> 01:51:30.347
"As Darwin put it, any
animal, whatever endowed

01:51:30.347 --> 01:51:32.387
"with well-marked social instincts,

01:51:32.387 --> 01:51:35.627
"would inevitably acquire
a moral censor conscience

01:51:35.627 --> 01:51:37.907
"as soon as its intellectual
powers had become

01:51:37.907 --> 01:51:40.430
"as well developed as in man."

01:51:40.430 --> 01:51:43.550
That is the socio-biological
explanation for morality.

01:51:43.550 --> 01:51:46.510
The problem is that that
moral sense that develops

01:51:46.510 --> 01:51:49.640
in pig societies, chimpanzees, baboons,

01:51:49.640 --> 01:51:53.560
and Homo sapiens is
illusory on atheism because

01:51:53.560 --> 01:51:56.450
there are no objective
moral duties or values

01:51:56.450 --> 01:51:59.490
that we have to fulfill
and that's what the theist

01:51:59.490 --> 01:52:01.030
can offer Mr. Hitchens.

01:52:01.030 --> 01:52:03.360
And so, I want to invite Mr. Hitchens

01:52:03.360 --> 01:52:06.153
to think about becoming
a Christian tonight.

01:52:07.770 --> 01:52:12.720
[audience laughing]
[applause]

01:52:12.720 --> 01:52:16.050
Honestly, if he is a man
of good will who will

01:52:16.050 --> 01:52:17.450
follow the evidence where it leads,

01:52:17.450 --> 01:52:19.810
all of the evidence tonight
has been on one side

01:52:19.810 --> 01:52:22.600
of the scale and he
wants to affirm objective

01:52:22.600 --> 01:52:25.910
moral values so why not adopt theism?

01:52:25.910 --> 01:52:29.020
The resurrection of
Jesus has gone unrefuted.

01:52:29.020 --> 01:52:31.400
The argument is not
that it's too improbable

01:52:31.400 --> 01:52:33.870
to be false, the argument is that you need

01:52:33.870 --> 01:52:37.330
a historically sufficient
explanation to explain

01:52:37.330 --> 01:52:40.230
why the disciples came
to believe this and there

01:52:40.230 --> 01:52:43.100
isn't one apart from the
empty tomb and appearances.

01:52:43.100 --> 01:52:45.520
It's not a matter of rumor
because the empty tomb

01:52:45.520 --> 01:52:48.220
was public knowledge in Jerusalem.

01:52:48.220 --> 01:52:50.030
It would impossible for Christianity

01:52:50.030 --> 01:52:53.990
to flourish in Jerusalem in
the face of an occupied tomb.

01:52:53.990 --> 01:52:56.750
Finally, the immediate experience of God.

01:52:56.750 --> 01:52:58.510
If there's anyone watching or listening

01:52:58.510 --> 01:53:00.930
to the debate tonight who hasn't found God

01:53:00.930 --> 01:53:03.100
in a personal experiential way then I want

01:53:03.100 --> 01:53:06.230
to invite you as well to think
about becoming a Christian.

01:53:06.230 --> 01:53:09.010
I became a Christian as
a junior in high school

01:53:09.010 --> 01:53:11.190
and it changed my entire life

01:53:11.190 --> 01:53:13.430
and I believe that if
you'll look into it honestly

01:53:13.430 --> 01:53:15.620
with an open mind and
an open heart that it

01:53:15.620 --> 01:53:17.793
can change your life as well.

01:53:19.325 --> 01:53:24.325
[audience applause]
[cheering]

