Each participant will
answer every question.

01:54:02.850 --> 01:54:04.750
&gt;&gt; Dr. Craig, Mr. Hitchens,
thank you so much.

01:54:04.750 --> 01:54:06.830
It's been great listening to you both.

01:54:06.830 --> 01:54:08.573
My question is for Mr. Hitchens.

01:54:09.510 --> 01:54:13.107
Mr. Hitchens, in your book God
is Not Great, you say that,

01:54:13.107 --> 01:54:14.797
"There are four irreducible objections

01:54:14.797 --> 01:54:16.187
"to religious faith."

01:54:17.140 --> 01:54:18.877
The third being that religious faith

01:54:18.877 --> 01:54:21.307
"Is both the result and the cause

01:54:21.307 --> 01:54:23.527
"of dangerous sexual repression."

01:54:24.660 --> 01:54:26.840
So here's my question for you:

01:54:26.840 --> 01:54:28.444
Is it good that the Bible prohibits humans

01:54:28.444 --> 01:54:30.790
from having sex with animals,

01:54:30.790 --> 01:54:33.563
or is that an example of
dangerous sexual repression?

01:54:35.580 --> 01:54:38.823
&gt;&gt; Um.
[audience laughing]

01:54:41.070 --> 01:54:45.260
The allusion I was making
was not to the man-made,

01:54:45.260 --> 01:54:47.510
in the ordinary sense nature of religion,

01:54:47.510 --> 01:54:50.660
that you can tell from
studying some of its codes

01:54:50.660 --> 01:54:52.600
that it's, humans have invented it.

01:54:52.600 --> 01:54:55.140
That's why so many of the injunctions

01:54:55.140 --> 01:54:57.287
in the Old Testament are
as you quite rightly say,

01:54:57.287 --> 01:55:00.037
concerned with agriculture,
shall we put it delicately?

01:55:02.440 --> 01:55:04.980
But, it's more that it's man-made,

01:55:04.980 --> 01:55:09.530
it's designed to keep
women in subordination.

01:55:09.530 --> 01:55:10.980
&gt;&gt; Man: But could you answer the question?

01:55:10.980 --> 01:55:12.275
&gt;&gt; Yes.

01:55:12.275 --> 01:55:13.990
&gt;&gt; Do you think the Bible
is right to prohibit humans

01:55:13.990 --> 01:55:15.440
from having sex with animals?

01:55:16.290 --> 01:55:18.750
&gt;&gt; I don't know of any good advice about

01:55:18.750 --> 01:55:21.050
having sex with animals, in
favor of it, I mean to say.

01:55:21.050 --> 01:55:23.330
Look, there are things that if people do,

01:55:23.330 --> 01:55:26.700
incest is one and cannibalism is another,

01:55:26.700 --> 01:55:28.510
if you do them, you'll die out.

01:55:28.510 --> 01:55:30.740
A society that permitted it would.

01:55:30.740 --> 01:55:31.940
There were societies in New Guinea

01:55:31.940 --> 01:55:35.580
that did practice cannibalism
and there's a terrible

01:55:35.580 --> 01:55:37.500
disease that you get
called Kuru if you do it

01:55:37.500 --> 01:55:40.300
and it seems to me, if you like,

01:55:40.300 --> 01:55:42.550
there are some rules
that are self-enforcing.

01:55:44.530 --> 01:55:46.080
That's not what I, when I was talking

01:55:46.080 --> 01:55:47.597
about sexual repression,
I was talking about

01:55:47.597 --> 01:55:51.140
the enormous number of prohibitions on

01:55:51.140 --> 01:55:53.980
sex between men and women
and on the evident fear

01:55:53.980 --> 01:55:58.270
of female sexuality and
the superstitious dread,

01:55:58.270 --> 01:56:00.380
for example, of female menstrual blood.

01:56:00.380 --> 01:56:01.520
Things of this kind.

01:56:01.520 --> 01:56:04.810
&gt;&gt; Dr. Craig, your assessment
of that question and answer.

01:56:04.810 --> 01:56:07.460
&gt;&gt; Well, I think the
question illustrates that,

01:56:07.460 --> 01:56:11.773
apart from God, whatever
is in nature is right.

01:56:12.780 --> 01:56:16.260
There is no thing barred in nature

01:56:16.260 --> 01:56:19.650
if there is no sort of
objective moral code.

01:56:19.650 --> 01:56:22.790
So, the question is a good one because

01:56:22.790 --> 01:56:25.970
it illustrates that here is a guideline

01:56:25.970 --> 01:56:28.130
for sexual expression that is very good

01:56:28.130 --> 01:56:30.330
for human beings and not something that's

01:56:30.330 --> 01:56:34.130
meant to be repressive or
harmful to human beings.

01:56:34.130 --> 01:56:36.590
In fact, the studies I've seen says that

01:56:36.590 --> 01:56:39.370
religious people have more fun with sex

01:56:39.370 --> 01:56:42.260
than people who are not religious

01:56:42.260 --> 01:56:44.900
and it's actually shows that they are more

01:56:44.900 --> 01:56:47.690
sexually satisfied in
marriage and so forth.

01:56:47.690 --> 01:56:50.610
So I think the question
makes a good point.

01:56:50.610 --> 01:56:52.960
&gt;&gt; I think I have to have
another bite at this--

01:56:54.488 --> 01:56:57.640
[audience laughing]

01:56:57.640 --> 01:56:59.310
This tempting cherry.

01:56:59.310 --> 01:57:03.820
You see, if it's true
that, as I think it is,

01:57:03.820 --> 01:57:06.050
that nature is pretty
indifferent, pretty callous,

01:57:06.050 --> 01:57:08.920
pretty random, then who is the designer?

01:57:08.920 --> 01:57:11.810
Many people say, concerning
the ban on homosexuality,

01:57:11.810 --> 01:57:14.417
for example, in the Old
Testament, they'll say,

01:57:14.417 --> 01:57:16.097
"Well, homosexuality is against God's law

01:57:16.097 --> 01:57:17.970
"and against Nature's law."

01:57:17.970 --> 01:57:20.353
Well, in that case, why
does nature see to it

01:57:20.353 --> 01:57:23.310
that so many people are born homosexual?

01:57:23.310 --> 01:57:24.990
Or, if you want to rephrase it,

01:57:24.990 --> 01:57:26.868
why does God have so many of his children

01:57:26.868 --> 01:57:29.003
preferring sex with their own gender?

01:57:29.840 --> 01:57:32.130
It doesn't help, it doesn't, in clarifying

01:57:32.130 --> 01:57:33.473
and elucidating this.

01:57:33.473 --> 01:57:36.420
It doesn't help to assume
a supernatural authority.

01:57:36.420 --> 01:57:39.940
Whereas, if you look at the reasons given

01:57:39.940 --> 01:57:43.460
by Maimonides and the other sages for the

01:57:43.460 --> 01:57:47.850
practice of circumcision,
it is precisely to dull

01:57:47.850 --> 01:57:50.750
and to blunt the sensation of an organ

01:57:50.750 --> 01:57:52.163
which I don't think even,

01:57:53.570 --> 01:57:56.300
well, I'll leave it there.
[audience laughing]

01:57:56.300 --> 01:57:57.450
&gt;&gt; Hugh: Our next question.

01:57:57.450 --> 01:57:59.030
&gt;&gt; It's explicitly
designed, in other words,

01:57:59.030 --> 01:58:00.740
to reduce sexual pleasure,

01:58:00.740 --> 01:58:03.333
make it more of a painful
duty than a celebration.

01:58:06.480 --> 01:58:08.510
Well you asked for it.

01:58:08.510 --> 01:58:10.670
&gt;&gt; I don't want to misrepresent myself.

01:58:10.670 --> 01:58:13.577
I was a student here and graduated--

01:58:14.557 --> 01:58:17.557
[audience laughing]

01:58:19.470 --> 01:58:21.323
Somewhat by the skin of my teeth.

01:58:22.850 --> 01:58:26.510
Mr. Hitchens you stated that, some of your

01:58:26.510 --> 01:58:30.920
most strongly stated arguments are that

01:58:30.920 --> 01:58:35.920
the results of religion,
violence, death, destruction,

01:58:37.130 --> 01:58:39.413
the motivation being religion,

01:58:40.540 --> 01:58:45.540
discredit those who would
promote a belief in God.

01:58:47.020 --> 01:58:50.200
However, I think there's
an imbalance there

01:58:50.200 --> 01:58:54.840
in that the nuclear bomb
was created by physicists

01:58:54.840 --> 01:58:59.011
and is the most demonstrable violence

01:58:59.011 --> 01:59:01.240
perpetrated on mankind.

01:59:01.240 --> 01:59:04.540
So I wonder how you respond to that.

01:59:04.540 --> 01:59:06.520
&gt;&gt; Well physics isn't an ideology.

01:59:06.520 --> 01:59:08.060
Physics isn't a belief system.

01:59:08.060 --> 01:59:09.700
It's a science.

01:59:09.700 --> 01:59:11.120
&gt;&gt; Well that, I think
that would be subjective.

01:59:11.120 --> 01:59:13.080
&gt;&gt; I mean you could, any more than

01:59:15.160 --> 01:59:19.020
Marie Curie discovering radium makes

01:59:20.010 --> 01:59:22.470
her practice morally different.

01:59:22.470 --> 01:59:25.890
I mean, it's not comparing like with like.

01:59:25.890 --> 01:59:28.530
What I'm talking about
are specific religious

01:59:28.530 --> 01:59:30.140
injunctions to do evil.

01:59:30.140 --> 01:59:33.494
To mutilate the genitalia
of children, for example.

01:59:33.494 --> 01:59:37.370
To take the pastor, Douglas Wilson,

01:59:37.370 --> 01:59:39.340
who Dr. Craig was just mentioning,

01:59:39.340 --> 01:59:41.180
with whom I've crossed swords
several times this year,

01:59:41.180 --> 01:59:42.710
and recently in Dallas.

01:59:42.710 --> 01:59:44.310
I happened to be mentioning to him about

01:59:44.310 --> 01:59:46.910
the commandment to
exterminate the Amalekites

01:59:46.910 --> 01:59:48.540
in one of our debates and
he said that commandment

01:59:48.540 --> 01:59:49.403
is still valid.

01:59:50.690 --> 01:59:51.890
If there were any Amalekites

01:59:51.890 --> 01:59:53.490
it would be his job to
make sure they were all

01:59:53.490 --> 01:59:57.960
put to the sword and some
of the virgins left over

01:59:57.960 --> 02:00:00.220
for slavery, purposes better imagined

02:00:00.220 --> 02:00:02.070
perhaps than described.

02:00:02.070 --> 02:00:03.690
I think this is a very serious problem.

02:00:03.690 --> 02:00:06.380
I'm not taking refuge in the common place

02:00:06.380 --> 02:00:10.010
that sometimes religious
people behave badly

02:00:10.010 --> 02:00:11.430
and that that would discredit religion.

02:00:11.430 --> 02:00:12.930
That would be a very soft option.

02:00:12.930 --> 02:00:15.520
I'm saying that there
are specific biblical,

02:00:15.520 --> 02:00:17.993
scriptural injunctions to do evil.

02:00:18.920 --> 02:00:21.010
&gt;&gt; Dr. Craig in that regards,

02:00:21.010 --> 02:00:23.990
those who are announced
atheists who have done evil

02:00:23.990 --> 02:00:26.730
in the world particularly
in the last 20th century,

02:00:26.730 --> 02:00:29.990
the Marxists, the
Trotskyites, the Stalinists.

02:00:29.990 --> 02:00:31.660
have they done more damage in your view

02:00:31.660 --> 02:00:33.230
and more evil than Christians?

02:00:33.230 --> 02:00:35.220
&gt;&gt; Well, this is a debate, Hugh,

02:00:35.220 --> 02:00:36.970
that I don't want to get into

02:00:36.970 --> 02:00:38.753
because I think it's irrelevant.

02:00:39.805 --> 02:00:41.940
I, as a philosopher, and I mean this,

02:00:41.940 --> 02:00:46.380
am interested in the
truth of these world views

02:00:46.380 --> 02:00:49.550
more than I'm interested
in the social impact.

02:00:49.550 --> 02:00:52.560
And you cannot judge the
truth of a world view

02:00:52.560 --> 02:00:55.660
by its social impact,
that's just irrelevant.

02:00:55.660 --> 02:00:58.650
Bertrand Russell, in his essay
"Why I'm Not a Christian"

02:00:58.650 --> 02:00:59.483
understood this.

02:00:59.483 --> 02:01:03.080
Russell said you cannot assess the truth

02:01:03.080 --> 02:01:05.540
of a world view by
seeing whether it's good

02:01:05.540 --> 02:01:07.000
for society or not.

02:01:07.000 --> 02:01:09.410
Now the irony was when
Russell wrote that back

02:01:09.410 --> 02:01:12.870
in the '20s, he was trying to refute those

02:01:12.870 --> 02:01:16.010
who said that you should
be believe in Christianity

02:01:16.010 --> 02:01:19.130
because it's so socially
beneficial to society.

02:01:19.130 --> 02:01:20.450
It was just the mirror image of

02:01:20.450 --> 02:01:22.070
Christopher Hitchens' argument,

02:01:22.070 --> 02:01:24.230
where he's saying you
shouldn't believe in it because

02:01:24.230 --> 02:01:27.860
it's so socially detrimental
to human culture.

02:01:27.860 --> 02:01:30.470
But I think Russell's point cuts both ways

02:01:30.470 --> 02:01:32.120
because it's a valid point.

02:01:32.120 --> 02:01:34.900
You can't assess the truth of a world view

02:01:34.900 --> 02:01:38.240
by arguing about its
cultural and social impact.

02:01:38.240 --> 02:01:42.020
There are true ideas that may have had

02:01:42.020 --> 02:01:45.350
negative social impact and
therefore we have to deal

02:01:45.350 --> 02:01:46.610
with the truth of these,

02:01:46.610 --> 02:01:48.650
the arguments for and against them

02:01:48.650 --> 02:01:50.730
and not get into arguments about has

02:01:50.730 --> 02:01:54.060
Marxism or Chinese
Communism been responsible

02:01:54.060 --> 02:01:57.100
for more deaths than theism
in the twentieth century?

02:01:57.100 --> 02:01:59.720
&gt;&gt; No, I completely concur
with what you say there.

02:01:59.720 --> 02:02:02.370
I mean, I just wanted to say that I think

02:02:02.370 --> 02:02:05.070
those commandments are
injunctions to do evil

02:02:05.070 --> 02:02:08.100
but I would much prefer
to say that the tribe

02:02:08.100 --> 02:02:10.780
that thought it was hearing
these instructions from God,

02:02:10.780 --> 02:02:13.160
to kill all of its rivals,
exterminate all its rivals

02:02:13.160 --> 02:02:16.070
for the Holy Land,
might possibly have had,

02:02:16.070 --> 02:02:19.140
I think it's overwhelmingly
probable it did have,

02:02:19.140 --> 02:02:22.390
the need to seek and claim divine approval

02:02:22.390 --> 02:02:24.860
for the war of greedy extermination,

02:02:24.860 --> 02:02:27.000
annexation, and racist conquests that

02:02:27.000 --> 02:02:28.930
it was going to undertake anyway.

02:02:28.930 --> 02:02:30.700
In other words, I don't think there was

02:02:30.700 --> 02:02:32.800
an authority issuing
that commandment whether

02:02:32.800 --> 02:02:35.023
it was morally good or otherwise,

02:02:35.900 --> 02:02:37.180
as a matter of the truth.

02:02:37.180 --> 02:02:39.980
But I would add, and
I think the concession

02:02:39.980 --> 02:02:41.540
is very well worth having,

02:02:41.540 --> 02:02:42.990
that there is absolutely
no proof at all that

02:02:42.990 --> 02:02:45.370
Christianity makes people behave better.

02:02:45.370 --> 02:02:46.710
&gt;&gt; Wait a minute, I didn't concede that.

02:02:46.710 --> 02:02:49.400
I said I wasn't going to argue that,

02:02:49.400 --> 02:02:52.980
because it's irrelevant but by
no means did I concede that.

02:02:52.980 --> 02:02:55.520
And I do appreciate as
well the way you framed

02:02:55.520 --> 02:02:57.140
the issue the about the Canaanites.

02:02:57.140 --> 02:02:59.370
I think you're quite right in saying

02:02:59.370 --> 02:03:02.860
that this is not an issue about
whether or not God exists.

02:03:02.860 --> 02:03:06.110
Rather this is a question
about biblical inerrancy.

02:03:06.110 --> 02:03:09.090
Did these ancient Israelites
get it right in thinking

02:03:09.090 --> 02:03:12.150
that God had commanded them to
do these things or did they,

02:03:12.150 --> 02:03:13.680
in their nationalistic fervor,

02:03:13.680 --> 02:03:16.520
think God is on our side
and do something which,

02:03:16.520 --> 02:03:19.140
in fact, they weren't
commanded to do by God?

02:03:19.140 --> 02:03:23.340
So that this isn't an issue
between atheism and theism.

02:03:23.340 --> 02:03:25.930
This is an issue about
biblical inspiration

02:03:25.930 --> 02:03:28.980
and inerrancy and that's
an important issue,

02:03:28.980 --> 02:03:33.440
but it's not one that
is on the floor tonight.

02:03:33.440 --> 02:03:35.660
&gt;&gt; Our next student question.

02:03:35.660 --> 02:03:38.830
&gt;&gt; Hi, my question is mainly
directed at Mr. Hitchens, but,

02:03:38.830 --> 02:03:41.200
Christian theism, as with all theisms

02:03:41.200 --> 02:03:43.906
that claim a revelation
say that the purpose

02:03:43.906 --> 02:03:47.290
of human existence is to serve God,

02:03:47.290 --> 02:03:51.200
and Dr. Craig might want to
expound on that in some way.

02:03:51.200 --> 02:03:54.100
But Mr. Hitchens, as an atheist with no

02:03:54.100 --> 02:03:57.640
transcendent being giving
you a reason for existence,

02:03:57.640 --> 02:04:00.300
what then is the best way to live life

02:04:00.300 --> 02:04:02.850
or what is motivation for living life

02:04:02.850 --> 02:04:05.680
or what is the purpose of your existence

02:04:05.680 --> 02:04:08.280
without a transcendent being
telling you what to do?

02:04:09.636 --> 02:04:10.890
&gt;&gt; Well I find it, you
see this is where I find

02:04:12.484 --> 02:04:14.070
it hard to accept the
grammar of your question.

02:04:14.070 --> 02:04:16.667
It's as if, if I was
only willing to concede

02:04:16.667 --> 02:04:20.190
the supernatural, you
want to say transcendent,

02:04:20.190 --> 02:04:22.880
I want to say supernatural,
then my life would have purpose.

02:04:22.880 --> 02:04:25.043
I think that's a complete non sequitur.

02:04:26.280 --> 02:04:28.680
To me, at any rate, I'll have
to just make the confession.

02:04:28.680 --> 02:04:30.880
This is as real to me subjectively

02:04:30.880 --> 02:04:34.400
as any William Jamesian
apprehension of the divine.

02:04:34.400 --> 02:04:37.013
I don't get your point at all.

02:04:38.670 --> 02:04:40.750
&gt;&gt; Dr. Craig, one of the
written questions says,

02:04:40.750 --> 02:04:42.530
and I think it is
consistent with the question

02:04:42.530 --> 02:04:43.507
from the audience:

02:04:43.507 --> 02:04:45.913
"You've written that life
without God is absurd,

02:04:47.187 --> 02:04:48.697
"but I know unbelievers who are living

02:04:48.697 --> 02:04:50.077
"fulfilling moral lives.

02:04:50.077 --> 02:04:52.360
"In what way is their life absurd?"

02:04:52.360 --> 02:04:55.410
&gt;&gt; Okay, let me respond to
that and to the question,

02:04:55.410 --> 02:04:56.243
here that was asked.

02:04:56.243 --> 02:04:59.310
I would say that the purpose of life,

02:04:59.310 --> 02:05:00.580
for which God has created us,

02:05:00.580 --> 02:05:02.520
is not to serve God.

02:05:02.520 --> 02:05:05.557
Remember, Jesus said, "I
have not called you servants,

02:05:05.557 --> 02:05:07.500
"I have called you friends."

02:05:07.500 --> 02:05:09.750
And I think the Westminster
Confession gets it right

02:05:09.750 --> 02:05:11.650
when it says the purpose
of human existence

02:05:11.650 --> 02:05:16.160
is to glorify God and enjoy Him forever.

02:05:16.160 --> 02:05:18.640
God is the fulfillment of human existence.

02:05:18.640 --> 02:05:21.130
It is in fellowship eternally with God,

02:05:21.130 --> 02:05:23.710
the source of infinite goodness and love,

02:05:23.710 --> 02:05:26.796
that the true fulfillment
of human existence

02:05:26.796 --> 02:05:29.410
and freedom is to be found.

02:05:29.410 --> 02:05:34.070
Now, when I say that, apart from theism,

02:05:34.070 --> 02:05:38.110
life is meaningless, I mean
objectively meaningless.

02:05:38.110 --> 02:05:40.520
This is the same distinction
that we're talking

02:05:40.520 --> 02:05:42.740
about with regard to moral values.

02:05:42.740 --> 02:05:44.470
I'm saying that on atheism,

02:05:44.470 --> 02:05:49.470
there is there is no objective
purpose for human existence.

02:05:49.600 --> 02:05:51.120
As Mr. Hitchens recognizes,

02:05:51.120 --> 02:05:56.120
eventually the universe will
grow cold, dilute, dark,

02:05:57.550 --> 02:06:01.120
and dead as it runs down
toward maximum entropy

02:06:01.120 --> 02:06:04.380
and heat death and all human existence

02:06:04.380 --> 02:06:09.380
and life will be extinguished
on an atheistic view

02:06:09.520 --> 02:06:10.750
of the future of the universe.

02:06:10.750 --> 02:06:13.320
There is no purpose for
which the universe exists;

02:06:13.320 --> 02:06:16.080
the litter of a dead
universe will just expand

02:06:16.080 --> 02:06:18.090
into the endless darkness forever,

02:06:18.090 --> 02:06:19.860
a universe in ruins.

02:06:19.860 --> 02:06:22.859
Now, of course one can
still live one's life

02:06:22.859 --> 02:06:25.027
as an illusion, thinking,

02:06:25.027 --> 02:06:28.067
"Well, the purpose of life is to, say,

02:06:28.067 --> 02:06:31.107
"hit forty home runs and
steal 40 bases every year,

02:06:31.107 --> 02:06:32.380
"you know, in the major leagues,"

02:06:32.380 --> 02:06:34.630
and you draw the meaning of your existence

02:06:34.630 --> 02:06:36.440
from that but that's
not really the meaning

02:06:36.440 --> 02:06:39.960
of your existence, that's
just a subjective illusion.

02:06:39.960 --> 02:06:42.054
In fact, your existence on atheism

02:06:42.054 --> 02:06:45.250
is objectively meaningless.

02:06:45.250 --> 02:06:47.610
So that's the distinction
that I was making.

02:06:47.610 --> 02:06:51.343
Again, it's between objective
and mere subjective illusion.

02:06:52.940 --> 02:06:57.710
&gt;&gt; Well, I think it has it
exactly the wrong way around.

02:06:57.710 --> 02:07:00.140
You see, as I was
beginning to say earlier,

02:07:00.140 --> 02:07:01.960
we didn't have time in
the question period,

02:07:01.960 --> 02:07:04.670
I wouldn't say that atheism
was morally inferior,

02:07:04.670 --> 02:07:05.970
I wouldn't concede that for a second.

02:07:05.970 --> 02:07:09.530
I don't want to make a claim
for its superiority either,

02:07:09.530 --> 02:07:11.810
but there may be a slight edge here.

02:07:11.810 --> 02:07:14.693
We don't believe anything
that could be called wishful.

02:07:16.160 --> 02:07:18.050
In other words, we don't
particularly welcome

02:07:18.050 --> 02:07:21.540
the idea of the annihilation
either of ourselves,

02:07:21.540 --> 02:07:22.373
as individuals.

02:07:22.373 --> 02:07:24.590
The party will go one, we will have left

02:07:24.590 --> 02:07:26.430
and we're not coming back.

02:07:26.430 --> 02:07:29.273
Or of the entropic heat
death of the universe.

02:07:29.273 --> 02:07:31.270
We don't like the idea,

02:07:31.270 --> 02:07:33.070
but there's a good deal
of evidence to suggest

02:07:33.070 --> 02:07:34.710
that is what's gonna happen.

02:07:34.710 --> 02:07:37.120
And there's very, very
little evidence to suggest

02:07:37.120 --> 02:07:40.673
that I'll see you all
again in some theme park.

02:07:42.690 --> 02:07:45.210
One nice and one nasty experience.

02:07:45.210 --> 02:07:47.170
There's absolutely no
evidence for that at all.

02:07:47.170 --> 02:07:49.960
So I'm willing to accept
on the evidence conclusions

02:07:49.960 --> 02:07:51.920
that may be unwelcome to me.

02:07:51.920 --> 02:07:55.080
I'm sorry if I sound as
if I'm spelling that out,

02:07:55.080 --> 02:07:55.990
but I will.

02:07:55.990 --> 02:07:58.290
Now you want to know what
makes my life meaningful?

02:07:58.290 --> 02:08:01.720
Generally speaking it's
been struggling myself

02:08:01.720 --> 02:08:04.150
to be free and, if I can
say it without immodesty,

02:08:04.150 --> 02:08:06.330
Mr. Hewitt kindly said it for me,

02:08:06.330 --> 02:08:09.190
too flatteringly beforehand,

02:08:09.190 --> 02:08:11.240
but trying to help others to be free too.

02:08:13.040 --> 02:08:15.057
That's what's given a
lot of meaning to my life

02:08:15.057 --> 02:08:16.230
and does still.

02:08:16.230 --> 02:08:21.230
Solidarity with those who
want to be as free as I am,

02:08:22.290 --> 02:08:25.285
partly by luck and partly by my own

02:08:25.285 --> 02:08:26.980
efforts and the efforts of others.

02:08:26.980 --> 02:08:30.010
Well one obstacle to liberty,

02:08:30.010 --> 02:08:32.020
and that's why I mentioned it

02:08:32.020 --> 02:08:33.920
and gave so many examples of it in history

02:08:33.920 --> 02:08:35.430
and in the present day,

02:08:35.430 --> 02:08:38.190
is the poisonous role
played by fellow primates

02:08:38.190 --> 02:08:41.064
of mine who think they
can tell me what to do

02:08:41.064 --> 02:08:43.470
in the name of God because God's told them

02:08:43.470 --> 02:08:45.470
that they have this power.

02:08:45.470 --> 02:08:49.550
So, that's one thing I'd
like to be shot of right here

02:08:49.550 --> 02:08:50.383
in the here in now.

02:08:50.383 --> 02:08:53.050
And my suspicion is, if you
really ask the religious

02:08:53.050 --> 02:08:55.480
whether they want power
and what's the world

02:08:55.480 --> 02:08:58.040
they care about, the next one or this one,

02:08:58.040 --> 02:08:59.940
it'll be this one every time,

02:08:59.940 --> 02:09:02.143
because they too know perfectly well

02:09:02.143 --> 02:09:04.720
that this is the only life we've got.

02:09:04.720 --> 02:09:06.020
&gt;&gt; Yeah, I don't think that's true.

02:09:06.020 --> 02:09:07.173
It seems to me that,

02:09:08.820 --> 02:09:11.210
on the basis of the resurrection of Jesus

02:09:11.210 --> 02:09:14.840
that we have grounds for
the hope of immortality.

02:09:14.840 --> 02:09:16.860
This is the foundation upon which the

02:09:16.860 --> 02:09:18.690
Christian hope is predicated.

02:09:18.690 --> 02:09:21.450
So, again, it gets back to whether or not

02:09:21.450 --> 02:09:24.350
one has good grounds for thinking

02:09:24.350 --> 02:09:25.700
that Jesus was who he claimed to be

02:09:25.700 --> 02:09:27.770
and that God raised him from the dead

02:09:27.770 --> 02:09:32.210
because if he did, then
there is hope of immortality.

02:09:32.210 --> 02:09:35.350
&gt;&gt; But then, I return your question to me,

02:09:35.350 --> 02:09:37.540
I return it to you in a different form.

02:09:37.540 --> 02:09:40.840
If there's going to be a resurrection,

02:09:40.840 --> 02:09:42.850
an ingathering, if in the
end all the injustices

02:09:42.850 --> 02:09:45.250
will be canceled, all tears dried,

02:09:45.250 --> 02:09:46.420
all the other promises kept,

02:09:46.420 --> 02:09:48.970
then why do you care what
happens in this brief

02:09:48.970 --> 02:09:49.803
veil of tears?

02:09:49.803 --> 02:09:51.500
Why do the churches want
power in the here and now?

02:09:51.500 --> 02:09:53.850
Why do they want to
legislate for things like

02:09:53.850 --> 02:09:56.360
abortion or sexuality or morality?

02:09:56.360 --> 02:09:57.390
Why bother?

02:09:57.390 --> 02:10:00.100
I mean, isn't it just as much the case,

02:10:00.100 --> 02:10:02.300
as Dostoyevsky says about atheism,

02:10:02.300 --> 02:10:04.940
that without God all things are possible,

02:10:04.940 --> 02:10:07.310
that with God all things
are thinkable too?

02:10:07.310 --> 02:10:08.230
&gt;&gt; Not at all.

02:10:08.230 --> 02:10:11.700
As Dostoyevsky said, if
there is no immortality,

02:10:11.700 --> 02:10:13.810
all things are permitted, he said,

02:10:13.810 --> 02:10:15.430
because it all ends up the same,

02:10:15.430 --> 02:10:17.650
it all comes out in the wash the same.

02:10:17.650 --> 02:10:19.920
But, if there is a God who exists,

02:10:19.920 --> 02:10:22.140
who loves human beings
and has created them

02:10:22.140 --> 02:10:25.830
in his image and endowed them
with intrinsic moral value

02:10:25.830 --> 02:10:27.840
and unalienable rights,

02:10:27.840 --> 02:10:32.010
then you have every reason
to treasure other persons

02:10:32.010 --> 02:10:33.720
as ends in themselves.

02:10:33.720 --> 02:10:36.937
And the desire of pro-life

02:10:38.710 --> 02:10:41.820
persons to champion
the lives of the unborn

02:10:41.820 --> 02:10:45.750
or the lives of the
dying isn't a power grab,

02:10:45.750 --> 02:10:48.180
Mr. Hitchens, it's because they genuinely

02:10:48.180 --> 02:10:51.870
care about the lives of
innocent human beings

02:10:51.870 --> 02:10:55.203
that they believe are
being wantonly destroyed.

02:10:56.498 --> 02:10:57.598
[audience applause]

02:10:57.598 --> 02:10:59.483
So it's a very positive motivation.

02:11:03.590 --> 02:11:05.019
&gt;&gt; Agreed, agreed, but there are perfectly

02:11:05.019 --> 02:11:07.967
good humanist motives for
doing all those things

02:11:07.967 --> 02:11:10.200
and if you want to have
a reason for caring

02:11:10.200 --> 02:11:12.510
about the survival and health
and well being of others,

02:11:12.510 --> 02:11:14.150
the idea that you might depend on them

02:11:14.150 --> 02:11:15.620
for the only life you've got,

02:11:15.620 --> 02:11:17.550
and they on you for solidarity,

02:11:17.550 --> 02:11:20.790
is just as good an
explanation for right action.

02:11:20.790 --> 02:11:21.641
&gt;&gt; William: Now don't you--

02:11:21.641 --> 02:11:25.510
&gt;&gt; Par contre, if people
think God is telling

02:11:25.510 --> 02:11:29.250
them what to do, or they
have God on their side,

02:11:29.250 --> 02:11:30.910
what will they not do?

02:11:30.910 --> 02:11:32.380
That's what I meant by the reverse of

02:11:32.380 --> 02:11:33.500
the Dostoyevsky question.

02:11:33.500 --> 02:11:35.500
What crime will not be committed?

02:11:35.500 --> 02:11:39.500
What offense to justice
and to reason will not be,

02:11:39.500 --> 02:11:42.310
is not regularly committed
by people who are convinced

02:11:42.310 --> 02:11:44.689
that it is God's will that they do that?

02:11:44.689 --> 02:11:45.663
It's with God that all is possible.

02:11:45.663 --> 02:11:46.500
&gt;&gt; If they commit such
atrocities it is only

02:11:46.500 --> 02:11:48.480
because they only act inconsistently

02:11:48.480 --> 02:11:50.690
with their world view
rather than in line with it.

02:11:50.690 --> 02:11:53.880
Jesus would not have
been a guard at Auschwitz

02:11:53.880 --> 02:11:58.010
or someone who would take
away the human rights

02:11:58.010 --> 02:11:58.930
of another person.

02:11:58.930 --> 02:12:02.900
You need to ask what kinds of actions

02:12:02.900 --> 02:12:05.230
are sanctioned by a world view?

02:12:05.230 --> 02:12:07.710
And on atheism, as Dostoyevsky said,

02:12:07.710 --> 02:12:09.570
it seems everything is permitted.

02:12:09.570 --> 02:12:13.090
Humanism, without God
as a basis for humanism,

02:12:13.090 --> 02:12:15.950
is just a form of speciesism,

02:12:15.950 --> 02:12:18.370
a bias in favor of your own species.

02:12:18.370 --> 02:12:23.370
I think Christianity affirms
the real basis for humanism.

02:12:23.900 --> 02:12:27.160
&gt;&gt; Auschwitz is the outcome of centuries

02:12:27.160 --> 02:12:31.470
in which the Christian
Church announced, believed,

02:12:31.470 --> 02:12:33.220
that the Jewish people
had called for the blood

02:12:33.220 --> 02:12:35.810
of Jesus of Nazareth to be on their head

02:12:35.810 --> 02:12:38.020
for every generation.

02:12:38.020 --> 02:12:39.380
It's only in one verse in the Bible,

02:12:39.380 --> 02:12:40.540
I know, but it happens to be the verse

02:12:40.540 --> 02:12:42.240
the Church picked up on.

02:12:42.240 --> 02:12:43.980
I don't say Jesus would
have been a guard there,

02:12:43.980 --> 02:12:45.730
that's not the point,
the point is that this

02:12:45.730 --> 02:12:47.950
is not an aberration of religion,

02:12:47.950 --> 02:12:50.210
it is a scriptural injunction

02:12:50.210 --> 02:12:52.130
as is the one to kill the Amalekites--

02:12:52.130 --> 02:12:53.410
&gt;&gt; No, there's no scriptural--

02:12:53.410 --> 02:12:54.450
&gt;&gt; Christopher: As is the one to mutilate

02:12:54.450 --> 02:12:56.630
the genitals of children.

02:12:56.630 --> 02:12:57.463
&gt;&gt; It is.

02:12:57.463 --> 02:12:59.050
The issue is would Jesus have been

02:12:59.050 --> 02:13:01.860
a guard at Auschwitz
because insofar as people

02:13:01.860 --> 02:13:05.960
who claim to be his followers
were guards at Auschwitz,

02:13:05.960 --> 02:13:07.900
they were acting inconsistently

02:13:07.900 --> 02:13:10.717
and in defiance of the
ethic of Jesus of Nazareth.

02:13:10.717 --> 02:13:11.920
&gt;&gt; Well you should tell
that to the Vatican.

02:13:11.920 --> 02:13:14.160
I mean we know, Paul Johnson and his

02:13:14.160 --> 02:13:19.160
very friendly history of
Christianity says that,

02:13:20.440 --> 02:13:24.240
up to 50 to 60% of the
Waffen-SS were practicing,

02:13:24.240 --> 02:13:27.260
confessing Catholics in good standing.

02:13:27.260 --> 02:13:29.490
No one was ever threatened with discipline

02:13:29.490 --> 02:13:31.670
by the church with
excommunication, for example,

02:13:31.670 --> 02:13:33.710
for taking part in the Final Solution.

02:13:33.710 --> 02:13:36.290
The only Nazi ever
excommunicated by the church

02:13:36.290 --> 02:13:39.090
was Joseph Goebbels and, if
you like, I'll tell you why.

02:13:40.240 --> 02:13:41.073
&gt;&gt; Hugh: To the student.

02:13:41.073 --> 02:13:43.523
&gt;&gt; His wife was a divorced Protestant.

02:13:45.230 --> 02:13:46.063
&gt;&gt; Hugh: He was going to tell us anyway.

02:13:46.063 --> 02:13:49.090
&gt;&gt; Excuse, excuse me, Christianity
does have some standards.

02:13:49.090 --> 02:13:49.923
&gt;&gt; Next student.

02:13:52.638 --> 02:13:53.640
&gt;&gt; Hi, I'd just like
to thank both you guys

02:13:53.640 --> 02:13:55.320
for being here and in
the interest of fairness,

02:13:55.320 --> 02:13:56.600
I know I'm playing devil's advocate here,

02:13:56.600 --> 02:14:00.040
pun intended, but I think
since almost all of the

02:14:00.040 --> 02:14:04.030
questions are going to be
directed towards Mr. Hitchens

02:14:04.030 --> 02:14:05.790
I think we should have on for Dr. Craig.

02:14:05.790 --> 02:14:08.000
&gt;&gt; Christopher: They're
all for both of us.

02:14:08.000 --> 02:14:09.960
&gt;&gt; For Dr. Craig, what do you think about

02:14:09.960 --> 02:14:12.630
Epicurus' argument that
if God is omnibenevolent,

02:14:12.630 --> 02:14:15.380
omniscient, and omnipotent,
if He knows about kids

02:14:15.380 --> 02:14:18.790
in Africa that are born with AIDS,

02:14:18.790 --> 02:14:20.270
what do you think about Him suggesting,

02:14:20.270 --> 02:14:23.230
like Him not intervening and
Him not changing that fact?

02:14:23.230 --> 02:14:25.560
That's a question that
I've always struggled with

02:14:25.560 --> 02:14:26.660
so I'm just wondering,

02:14:27.570 --> 02:14:29.070
could you expand on that and
I'd also like your input on it.

02:14:29.070 --> 02:14:29.903
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

02:14:29.903 --> 02:14:31.760
The Problem of Evil and Suffering

02:14:31.760 --> 02:14:34.900
has been greatly discussed by philosophers

02:14:34.900 --> 02:14:36.860
and I think there's been genuine progress

02:14:36.860 --> 02:14:40.810
made in this century on this problem.

02:14:40.810 --> 02:14:42.880
I think it's important to
distinguish between the

02:14:42.880 --> 02:14:45.760
intellectual problem of suffering

02:14:45.760 --> 02:14:48.087
and the emotional problem of suffering

02:14:48.087 --> 02:14:51.160
because these are quite
different from each other.

02:14:51.160 --> 02:14:53.500
In terms of the intellectual
problem of suffering,

02:14:53.500 --> 02:14:57.030
I think that there you
need to ask yourself

02:14:57.030 --> 02:15:01.230
is the atheist claiming, as Epicurus did,

02:15:01.230 --> 02:15:05.790
that the existence of God
is logically incompatible

02:15:05.790 --> 02:15:08.080
with the evil and suffering in the world?

02:15:08.080 --> 02:15:09.970
If that's what the
atheist is claiming then

02:15:09.970 --> 02:15:12.100
he's got to be presupposing some kind

02:15:12.100 --> 02:15:14.530
of hidden assumptions that would bring out

02:15:14.530 --> 02:15:16.660
that contradiction and make it explicit

02:15:16.660 --> 02:15:20.690
because these statements are
not explicitly contradictory.

02:15:20.690 --> 02:15:22.950
The problem is no
philosopher in the history

02:15:22.950 --> 02:15:24.760
of the world has ever
been able to identify

02:15:24.760 --> 02:15:27.130
what those hidden
assumptions would be that

02:15:27.130 --> 02:15:29.650
would bring out the contradiction
and make it explicit.

02:15:29.650 --> 02:15:32.350
On the contrary, you can actually prove

02:15:32.350 --> 02:15:35.230
that these are logically
compatible with each other

02:15:35.230 --> 02:15:37.790
by adding a third proposition, namely,

02:15:37.790 --> 02:15:40.320
that God has morally sufficient reasons

02:15:40.320 --> 02:15:43.010
for permitting the evil in the world.

02:15:43.010 --> 02:15:46.700
As long as that statement
is even possibly true,

02:15:46.700 --> 02:15:49.540
it proves that there's no
logical incompatibility

02:15:49.540 --> 02:15:51.790
between God and the
suffering in the world.

02:15:51.790 --> 02:15:54.340
So the atheist would have to show that

02:15:54.340 --> 02:15:57.840
it is logically impossible
for God to have morally

02:15:57.840 --> 02:16:00.380
sufficient reasons for
permitting the evil and suffering

02:16:00.380 --> 02:16:03.360
in the world and no atheist
has ever been able to do that.

02:16:03.360 --> 02:16:06.270
So, that the logical
version of this problem,

02:16:06.270 --> 02:16:09.190
I think, is widely
recognized to have failed.

02:16:09.190 --> 02:16:11.230
Those atheists who still press the problem

02:16:11.230 --> 02:16:13.780
therefore press it as a
probabilistic argument.

02:16:13.780 --> 02:16:17.130
They try to say that, given
the evil in the world,

02:16:17.130 --> 02:16:19.250
it's improbable that God exists,

02:16:19.250 --> 02:16:21.860
not impossible but improbable.

02:16:21.860 --> 02:16:25.320
Well, again, the difficulty
there is that the atheist

02:16:25.320 --> 02:16:29.460
has to claim that if
God did exist then it is

02:16:29.460 --> 02:16:32.500
improbable that he would permit the evil

02:16:32.500 --> 02:16:34.270
and suffering in the world.

02:16:34.270 --> 02:16:37.140
And how could the atheist
possibly know that?

02:16:37.140 --> 02:16:41.510
How could the atheist
know that God would not,

02:16:41.510 --> 02:16:43.960
if He existed, permit the evil
and suffering in the world.

02:16:43.960 --> 02:16:46.440
Maybe He's got good reasons for it.

02:16:46.440 --> 02:16:49.070
Maybe, like in Christian theism,

02:16:49.070 --> 02:16:51.414
God's purpose for human
history is to bring

02:16:51.414 --> 02:16:54.550
the maximum number of people freely

02:16:54.550 --> 02:16:58.440
into his kingdom to find
salvation and eternal life

02:16:58.440 --> 02:17:00.770
and how do we know that
that wouldn't require

02:17:00.770 --> 02:17:04.350
a world that is simply
suffused with natural

02:17:04.350 --> 02:17:06.150
and moral suffering.

02:17:06.150 --> 02:17:08.270
It might be that only in a world like that

02:17:08.270 --> 02:17:10.510
the maximum number of
people would freely come

02:17:10.510 --> 02:17:12.900
to know God and find salvation.

02:17:12.900 --> 02:17:16.070
So the atheist would
have to show that there

02:17:16.070 --> 02:17:19.350
is a possible world
that's feasible for God

02:17:19.350 --> 02:17:21.330
which God could've created that would have

02:17:21.330 --> 02:17:24.450
just as much salvation and eternal life

02:17:24.450 --> 02:17:26.760
and knowledge of God as the actual world

02:17:26.760 --> 02:17:28.580
but with less suffering.

02:17:28.580 --> 02:17:30.430
And how could the atheist
prove such a thing?

02:17:30.430 --> 02:17:32.700
It's sheer speculation.

02:17:32.700 --> 02:17:36.170
So the problem is that, as an argument,

02:17:36.170 --> 02:17:41.170
the Problem of Evil makes
probability judgements

02:17:42.430 --> 02:17:45.810
which are very, very
ambitious and which we

02:17:45.810 --> 02:17:47.780
are simply not in a position to make

02:17:47.780 --> 02:17:49.620
with any kind of confidence.

02:17:49.620 --> 02:17:54.620
Now, I recognize that that
philosophical response

02:17:54.920 --> 02:17:57.470
to the question doesn't deal
with the emotional problem

02:17:57.470 --> 02:17:59.660
of evil and I think that for most people,

02:17:59.660 --> 02:18:01.610
this isn't really a philosophical problem,

02:18:01.610 --> 02:18:03.560
it's an emotional problem.

02:18:03.560 --> 02:18:06.665
They just don't like a god
who would permit suffering

02:18:06.665 --> 02:18:11.254
and pain in the world so
they turn their backs on him.

02:18:11.254 --> 02:18:13.950
What does Christianity have
to say to this problem?

02:18:13.950 --> 02:18:15.990
Well, I think it has a lot to say.

02:18:15.990 --> 02:18:17.980
It tells us that God is not some sort

02:18:17.980 --> 02:18:21.270
of an impersonal ground
of being or an indifferent

02:18:21.270 --> 02:18:25.058
tyrant who folds his arms
and watches the world suffer.

02:18:25.058 --> 02:18:28.720
Rather, He is a god who
enters into human history

02:18:28.720 --> 02:18:32.030
in the person of Jesus
Christ and what does He do?

02:18:32.030 --> 02:18:33.720
He suffers.

02:18:33.720 --> 02:18:37.490
On the cross, Christ
bore a suffering of which

02:18:37.490 --> 02:18:39.540
we can form no conception.

02:18:39.540 --> 02:18:42.880
Even though He was innocent,
He bore the penalty

02:18:42.880 --> 02:18:44.210
of the sins of the whole world.

02:18:44.210 --> 02:18:47.430
None of us can comprehend
what He suffered.

02:18:47.430 --> 02:18:51.630
And I think when we
contemplate the cross of Christ

02:18:51.630 --> 02:18:53.850
and His love for us
and what He was willing

02:18:53.850 --> 02:18:56.060
to undergo for us, it puts the problem

02:18:56.060 --> 02:18:58.940
of suffering in an entirely
different perspective.

02:18:58.940 --> 02:19:02.980
It means, I think, that
we can bear the suffering

02:19:02.980 --> 02:19:05.940
that God calls upon us
to endure in this life

02:19:05.940 --> 02:19:10.370
with courage and with
optimism for an eternal life

02:19:10.370 --> 02:19:13.900
of unending joy beyond the grave because

02:19:13.900 --> 02:19:16.450
of what Christ has done
for us and He will give us,

02:19:16.450 --> 02:19:19.660
I think, the courage and
the strength to get through

02:19:19.660 --> 02:19:22.700
the suffering that God calls
upon us to bear in this life.

02:19:22.700 --> 02:19:25.288
So, whether it's an emotional issue

02:19:25.288 --> 02:19:29.250
or intellectual issue I think ultimately

02:19:29.250 --> 02:19:31.120
Christian theism can make sense out of

02:19:31.120 --> 02:19:33.070
the suffering and evil in the world.

02:19:33.070 --> 02:19:34.880
&gt;&gt; As the clock winds down I reserve the

02:19:34.880 --> 02:19:36.970
last question for myself, Mr. Hitchens.

02:19:36.970 --> 02:19:38.240
&gt;&gt; Just on the devil's advocate point,

02:19:38.240 --> 02:19:41.470
when the Vatican asked me to
testify against Mother Teresa,

02:19:41.470 --> 02:19:43.210
I discovered, which I
did, I discovered that

02:19:43.210 --> 02:19:45.910
the office of devil's advocate
has been abolished now.

02:19:47.080 --> 02:19:48.970
So, I come before you as the only person

02:19:48.970 --> 02:19:51.170
ever to have represented
the devil pro bono.

02:19:52.607 --> 02:19:53.710
[audience laughing]

02:19:53.710 --> 02:19:54.620
&gt;&gt; Hugh: Last question.

02:19:54.620 --> 02:19:58.020
&gt;&gt; Yeah, now, I'm not one
of, I was very intrigued

02:19:58.020 --> 02:20:00.960
by that reply and largely agree with it.

02:20:00.960 --> 02:20:03.430
If I was a believer, I would not feel God

02:20:03.430 --> 02:20:04.780
owed me an explanation.

02:20:04.780 --> 02:20:06.340
I'm not one of those atheists who thinks

02:20:06.340 --> 02:20:08.660
you can go around saying, complaining,

02:20:08.660 --> 02:20:10.690
if you make the assumption
that there is a deity

02:20:10.690 --> 02:20:13.540
then all things are possible.

02:20:13.540 --> 02:20:16.008
You just have to be able
to make that assumption.

02:20:16.008 --> 02:20:17.770
At our debate in Dallas the other day

02:20:17.770 --> 02:20:21.030
I mentioned the case of FrÃ¤ulein Fritzl,

02:20:21.030 --> 02:20:23.180
the Austrian woman who was imprisoned

02:20:23.180 --> 02:20:24.830
in a dungeon by her father for quarter

02:20:24.830 --> 02:20:28.600
of a century and incestuously
raped and tortured

02:20:28.600 --> 02:20:31.437
and kept in the dark with
her children for 25 years

02:20:31.437 --> 02:20:33.670
and I thought, I asked
people to imagine how

02:20:33.670 --> 02:20:35.370
she must have beseeched him,

02:20:35.370 --> 02:20:36.840
how she must have begged him,

02:20:36.840 --> 02:20:38.350
and how the children must have,

02:20:38.350 --> 02:20:39.750
and how they must have prayed,

02:20:39.750 --> 02:20:42.030
and how those prayers went unanswered,

02:20:42.030 --> 02:20:44.007
and those beggings and
beseechments went unanswered

02:20:44.007 --> 02:20:46.993
for 25 years and, um,

02:20:48.220 --> 02:20:49.967
Douglas Wilson's reply to me was,

02:20:49.967 --> 02:20:51.420
"God will cancel all that

02:20:52.467 --> 02:20:53.920
"and all those tears will be dried,"

02:20:53.920 --> 02:20:56.290
and I said well if you're
capable of believing that

02:20:56.290 --> 02:20:59.240
then obviously what
that woman went through

02:20:59.240 --> 02:21:02.900
and what her children went
through was perfectly worth while

02:21:02.900 --> 02:21:05.930
and her father was all that
time, without knowing it,

02:21:05.930 --> 02:21:08.890
and apparently not
particularly wishing it,

02:21:08.890 --> 02:21:10.400
an instrument of the divine will

02:21:10.400 --> 02:21:12.780
and as I have said to
you before this evening,

02:21:12.780 --> 02:21:15.060
had occasion to say, you're perfectly free

02:21:15.060 --> 02:21:16.860
to believe that if you wish.

02:21:16.860 --> 02:21:18.000
&gt;&gt; Hugh: To conclude--

02:21:18.000 --> 02:21:18.833
&gt;&gt; I do.

02:21:18.833 --> 02:21:21.352
&gt;&gt; You could, Mr. Hitchens,

02:21:21.352 --> 02:21:22.740
you've got 4,000 people here,

02:21:22.740 --> 02:21:24.160
tens of thousands more watching.

02:21:24.160 --> 02:21:27.640
You could do the same exchange at Wheaton,

02:21:27.640 --> 02:21:31.220
at Westmont, at Azusa
Pacific, at Point Loma,

02:21:31.220 --> 02:21:33.230
at Notre Dame, at every
great Christian university

02:21:33.230 --> 02:21:34.760
in the United States, why do you think

02:21:34.760 --> 02:21:38.060
so many people come out to see debates

02:21:38.060 --> 02:21:40.663
with accomplished people
like Dr. Craig and you?

02:21:43.930 --> 02:21:48.430
&gt;&gt; It's a time for this great
question to come up again.

02:21:48.430 --> 02:21:50.343
I think there are two reasons for it.

02:21:51.300 --> 02:21:56.300
One is the emergence of a very aggressive

02:21:56.530 --> 02:21:59.983
theocratic challenge in
various parts of the world.

02:22:01.050 --> 02:22:05.730
We are about to see a
long-feared nightmare come true.

02:22:05.730 --> 02:22:08.900
The acquisition of apocalyptic weaponry

02:22:08.900 --> 02:22:12.720
by a Messianic regime in Tehran which

02:22:12.720 --> 02:22:14.880
is already enslaving and ruining

02:22:14.880 --> 02:22:16.763
a formerly great civilization.

02:22:17.880 --> 02:22:22.880
We see the forces of Al
Qaeda and related jihadists

02:22:23.180 --> 02:22:28.180
ruining the societies of Iraq,
of Afghanistan, Pakistan.

02:22:29.970 --> 02:22:34.090
We see Jewish settlers
stealing other people's land

02:22:34.090 --> 02:22:35.320
in the name of God in the hope that

02:22:35.320 --> 02:22:38.120
this will bring on a Messianic combat

02:22:38.120 --> 02:22:40.350
and of the return of the Messiah.

02:22:40.350 --> 02:22:42.490
And even in our own country we're not free

02:22:42.490 --> 02:22:45.170
from people who want to have stultifying

02:22:45.170 --> 02:22:47.180
nonsense taught to our children in school

02:22:47.180 --> 02:22:49.030
and in science class.

02:22:49.030 --> 02:22:52.210
So, there's that, it's
in the news all the time.

02:22:52.210 --> 02:22:54.120
And then there's the existence
of a very small group,

02:22:54.120 --> 02:22:56.050
of which I'm very proud to be a part,

02:22:56.050 --> 02:22:57.940
that says it's time to
take a stand against

02:22:57.940 --> 02:23:01.520
theocratic bullying and
is willing to go anywhere

02:23:01.520 --> 02:23:05.150
to debate these matters and
put these great questions

02:23:05.150 --> 02:23:06.990
to the proof, so.

02:23:06.990 --> 02:23:08.940
And thank you for giving me the chance.

02:23:10.716 --> 02:23:13.716
[audience applause]

02:23:18.980 --> 02:23:21.400
&gt;&gt; I would answer the
question somewhat differently.

02:23:21.400 --> 02:23:25.783
I think that what we're seeing
is the fruit of modernity.

02:23:26.810 --> 02:23:29.930
In the Enlightenment, the
Church and the Monarchy

02:23:29.930 --> 02:23:32.690
were thrown off in the
name of free thought

02:23:32.690 --> 02:23:35.470
and unshackled human inquiry.

02:23:35.470 --> 02:23:37.840
And the thought was that once mankind

02:23:37.840 --> 02:23:40.600
was freed from the shackles and bondage

02:23:40.600 --> 02:23:43.510
of religion that this would produce

02:23:43.510 --> 02:23:46.961
a sort of humanistic utopia.

02:23:46.961 --> 02:23:49.640
And instead I think what we've come to see

02:23:49.640 --> 02:23:53.330
is the fruit of the
naturalistic world view

02:23:53.330 --> 02:23:58.190
is that mankind is reduced
to meaninglessness,

02:23:58.190 --> 02:24:01.500
valuelessness, and
purposelessness and that

02:24:01.500 --> 02:24:03.670
therefore the question of God's existence

02:24:03.670 --> 02:24:06.660
has become all the more
poignant in our age

02:24:06.660 --> 02:24:09.250
because we're beginning
to question, I think,

02:24:09.250 --> 02:24:11.570
the fruit of modernity

02:24:11.570 --> 02:24:14.310
and questioning scientific naturalism.

02:24:14.310 --> 02:24:18.120
I'm privileged to be part of a revolution

02:24:18.120 --> 02:24:20.570
in Christian philosophy
that has been going on

02:24:20.570 --> 02:24:23.280
over the last half
century that has literally

02:24:23.280 --> 02:24:26.790
transformed the face of
Anglo-American philosophy.

02:24:26.790 --> 02:24:30.460
As the scientific, naturalistic,
atheistic world view

02:24:30.460 --> 02:24:34.750
has been challenged, in the
name of reason and philosophy,

02:24:34.750 --> 02:24:39.550
and the theistic world view reasserted,

02:24:39.550 --> 02:24:43.290
and I believe that we're
seeing a tremendous groundswell

02:24:43.290 --> 02:24:46.430
of interest among laypeople
as this revolution

02:24:46.430 --> 02:24:49.870
is beginning to filter down
to the man in the street.

02:24:49.870 --> 02:24:51.020
So I would see us

02:24:51.020 --> 02:24:56.020
as beginning to question the assumptions

02:24:57.230 --> 02:25:00.660
of modernity and the
bitter fruits of modernity

02:25:00.660 --> 02:25:04.260
that have been so evident
in the 20th century

02:25:04.260 --> 02:25:07.190
and I'm hoping that this will lead to

02:25:07.190 --> 02:25:09.990
a tremendous renaissance
in Christian thinking

02:25:09.990 --> 02:25:11.750
and Christian faith.

02:25:11.750 --> 02:25:15.427
&gt;&gt; To wrap up then--
